eeking to understand modern life in our increasingly mediated, globalized and binge-watching world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aFans (Persons). 0aPopular culturexPsychological aspects. 0aSubculture. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh1 aBennett, Lucy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBielby, Denise D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrooker, Will, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBusse, Kristina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCavicchi, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChatman, Dayna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChin, Bertha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClick, Melissa A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDe Kosnik, Abigail, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDuffett, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGilbert, Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGray, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGray, Jonathan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHarrington, C. Lee, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHeljakka, Katriina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHills, Matt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHitchcock Morimoto, Lori, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIto, Mizuko, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJenkins, Henry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators